                    <div class="faq-items-list">
                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4 class="faq-question">
                                Why list on the market if a cash offer is
                                faster?
                            </h4>
                            <p class="faq-answer">
                                If your house is already updated or you aren't
                                under a strict timeline, listing on the open
                                market exposes your property to traditional,
                                emotional retail buyers. This maximum exposure
                                drives competition for your home, helping you capture the
                                highest potential sale price.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4 class="faq-question">
                                How long does a traditional market listing take?
                            </h4>
                            <p class="faq-answer">
                                The timeline depends entirely on local buyer
                                demand, pricing strategy, and the condition of your home. While a direct cash sale can wrap up
                                in just a few days, an open market listing
                                usually averages between 30 to 90 days from the
                                initial launch to the closing.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4 class="faq-question">
                                How do you determine the listing price?
                            </h4>
                            <p class="faq-answer">
                                We analyze recent sales of similar homes,
                                current competition, local market conditions,
                                and your property's unique features to recommend
                                a pricing strategy. The right price helps
                                attract qualified buyers and maximize your
                                chances of receiving the strongest possible
                                offers.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
